0109|- [HelpText]
0111|*F1 codes:
0113|*F1 F1: Enter the Help system of Survo
0115|*F1 O:
0116|*When the cursor touches a pathname of a file, this file is opened
0117|*by a program associated in Windows to that file type.
0119|*F1 L:
0120|*lists the characters used in the control column of the current
0121|*edit field in alphabetic order. The characters will appear on a new
0122|*line inserted below the current edit line.
0123|*This facility helps in finding free characters for row labels.
0125|*F1 V:
0126|*When the cursor indicates a word which is a name of a variable in
0127|*the current active Survo data file, F1 V displays the extended form
0128|*of the name on the message line until ENTER is pressed or at most
0129|*for 10 seconds.
0131|*F1 codes (continued);
0133|*F1 #:
0134|*creates a fence structure for a command when the cursor is in the first
0135|*position of the command line and the command starts from that position.
0136|- shadow %: [LINK(q07_10.html)] [/LINK]
0137|*See FENCE?
S   |     %%%%%
0139|*F1 J:
0140|*is a generalization of F2 J.
0141|*It continues a phrase typed as first words on an edit line.
0143|- [New]
0144|*F1 <arrow_key>:
S   |    <         >
0145|*moves the cursor in the current edit field to
0146|*the last column in use (F1 RIGHT), the first column (F1 LEFT),
0147|*the last line (F1 DOWN), the first line (F1 UP).
0148|- [/New]
0150|*F1 codes (continued);
0152|- [New]
0153|*F1 A    starts the Survopoint display mode and
0154|*F1 a    interrupts that mode
0155|- [/New]
0157|*This mode enables displaying variable lines either systematically or
0158|*randomly on selected places in the main window of Survo.
